---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Ennyn"
  description="Why Ennyn exists, why now, who we are."
  register="a"
  activeNav="about"
  darkHero={true}
>
  <main class="about">

    <!-- DARK CINEMATIC HERO -->
    <section class="hero-dark">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <svg class="archway" viewBox="0 0 100 130" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M 18 130 L 18 50 A 32 32 0 0 1 82 50 L 82 130" stroke-width="1.2"/>
          <path d="M 28 130 L 28 56 A 22 22 0 0 1 72 56 L 72 130" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.45"/>
          <circle cx="50" cy="36" r="5" stroke-width="0.7"/>
          <circle cx="50" cy="36" r="1.4" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/>
          <line x1="50" y1="26" x2="50" y2="32" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.6"/>
          <line x1="50" y1="40" x2="50" y2="46" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.6"/>
          <line x1="40" y1="36" x2="46" y2="36" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.6"/>
          <line x1="54" y1="36" x2="60" y2="36" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.6"/>
          <line x1="10" y1="130" x2="90" y2="130" stroke-width="1.4"/>
          <line x1="4" y1="133.5" x2="96" y2="133.5" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4"/>
        </svg>
        <p class="kicker">About Ennyn</p>
        <h1>Why now.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Two software stacks. One disconnection. And finally,
          the technology to bridge it without rewriting either box.
        </p>
      </div>
      <span class="scroll-cue">↓ Read on</span>
    </section>

    <section class="body">
      <div class="wrap-narrow">
        <p class="lede">
          Until recently, getting an SMB onto modern back-office orchestration meant one
          of two bad options: pay for enterprise software they don't have the volume to
          justify, or hire an in-house ops team they can't afford. Most operators chose
          neither, and ran on a chain of manual handoffs across four vendors.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          Agentic AI platforms changed the economics. It's now viable to deliver
          enterprise-grade back-office orchestration as a service &mdash; an AI workflow
          team running an orchestration layer that bridges the systems an SMB already
          pays for, stood up in days, not quarters.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          That's the wedge. That's why Ennyn is possible now.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="team">
      <div class="wrap-narrow">
        <h2>Who we are.</h2>
        <p>
          We're a small team building Ennyn from operators' offices &mdash; not a product
          tour from the outside. More details when we're out of stealth.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <div class="wrap-narrow">
        <h2>Talk to us.</h2>
        <p>
          We're picking a small group of design partners. If your back office is held
          together by spreadsheets, post-its, and the memory of one operations manager,
          we'd like to hear about it.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href={`${base}/waitlist`} class="btn">Join the waitlist</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about > main > section:not(.hero-dark) {
    padding: 80px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .about .body {
    background: var(--paper);
    position: relative;
    margin-top: -40px;
    z-index: 2;
    padding-top: 56px !important;
  }
  .about h1 { margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .about h2 { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .about p.lede + p.lede { margin-top: 20px; }
  .about p + p { margin-top: 16px; }
  .about .cta .btn { margin-top: 16px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about > main > section:not(.hero-dark) { padding: 56px 0; }
    .about .body { margin-top: -20px; padding-top: 40px !important; }
  }
</style>
